combine pace and sprint as sprint (gait locomotion are essentially analogous)

combine shuffle and moonwalk and dance as dance (we dont want isolated motions and general motions whose intrinsic gait locomotion varies should be categorized into a general category)

combine walk and stride and strut and saunter and cross as walk (these may be different locomotions but are various forms of walking; end goal is to go into each verb and separate by its modifiers)

combine stumble and trip and startle as trip (startled is an adjective-verb that can lead to a motion similar to trip; a modifier)

combine crouch and crawl as crawl (crawl is an animated version of crouch; a modifer)

combine fall and recover as fall (fall is usually followed by recover)

